semantics.ranking

Class ExplainedRelationalRankingFunction

  • Object
    • RankingFunction<I>
      • ExplainedRankingFunction<RelationalAtom>
        • ExplainedRelationalRankingFunction

  • public class ExplainedRelationalRankingFunction
extends ExplainedRankingFunction<RelationalAtom>
    Extended version of RelationalRankingFunction that returns explanations for each evaluation. An evaluation tree is built with instances of Explanation.
    Author:
    Tobias Falke

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean accepts(Conditional<RelationalAtom> c, Explanation exp)
      Checks whether an open first-order conditional is accepted by the ranking function, which is the case if the conditional has at least one representative and a) the verification of the conditional has a lower rank than its falsification or b) both have the same rank, but all instantiations of the falsification formula with the conditionals representatives have lower ranks than all instantiations of the verification formula with representatives of the negated conditional.
      boolean accepts(Formula<RelationalAtom> f, Explanation exp)
      Checks whether an open first-order formula F is accepted by the ranking function, which is the case if the open conditional (F|true) is accepted.
      boolean accepts(RelationalKnowledgeBase kb)
      Checks whether a first-order knowledge base KB= is accepted by the ranking function, which is the case if all worlds not satisfying the set of facts are ranked with RankingFunction.INFINITY, and all conditionals are accepted.
      int getRank(Conditional<RelationalAtom> c, Explanation exp)
      Returns the rank for an open first-order conditional, which is the minimal rank of all of its instantiations, or RankingFunction.INFINITY, if there is no such instantiation.
      int getRank(Formula<RelationalAtom> f, Explanation exp)
      Returns the rank for an open first-order formula, which is the minimal rank of all of its possible instantiations, or RankingFunction.INFINITY, if there is no such instantiation.
      Collection<Constant> getRepresentatives(RelationalConditional c, Explanation exp)
      Returns the set of representatives for an open conditional.
      Collection<Constant> getWeakRepresentatives(RelationalConditional c, Explanation exp)
      Returns all weak representatives for an open conditional.
